00:50:48,573 --> 00:50:51,414
And were we giving a different set of rewards when it was

1133
00:50:51,454 --> 00:50:53,835
going to be an end game activity?

1134
00:50:54,235 --> 00:50:57,436
And while we had ideas on paper, nothing had been

1135
00:50:57,456 --> 00:50:58,076
decided yet.

1136
00:50:58,536 --> 00:51:02,378
So the investment portion, the reward portion, really came

1137
00:51:02,618 --> 00:51:04,258
after that decision to open it up to more

1138
00:51:04,298 --> 00:51:05,038
people had been made.

1139
00:51:05,379 --> 00:51:08,820
We were fortunate in that it took about, it was a 15 month

1140
00:51:08,840 --> 00:51:10,800
development cycle, roughly, for Gambit.

1141
00:51:11,721 --> 00:51:13,103
starting with a core small team

1142
00:51:13,123 --> 00:51:14,324
and then getting bigger and bigger and bigger

1143
00:51:14,344 --> 00:51:15,405
as we got deeper into production.

1144
00:51:15,745 --> 00:51:18,368
And so we had a playable game fairly early.

1145
00:51:18,729 --> 00:51:20,511
The pivot didn't come all that late.

1146
00:51:20,631 --> 00:51:21,952
So we still had plenty of time

1147
00:51:22,113 --> 00:51:24,675
after deciding to not make it be an end game ritual

1148
00:51:24,956 --> 00:51:28,119
to respond to that and craft the reward system afterwards.

1149
00:51:29,261 --> 00:51:29,541
Thank you.

