1196
00:53:39,320 --> 00:53:42,222
then we had that core group of four or five people

1197
00:53:42,302 --> 00:53:43,622
who were on board from the beginning.

1198
00:53:43,682 --> 00:53:46,004
And how were they decided, what disciplines and who?

1199
00:53:46,704 --> 00:53:48,425
It was kind of who was available at that time,

1200
00:53:48,485 --> 00:53:50,285
because you have to remember that D2

1201
00:53:50,646 --> 00:53:51,646
was still under production.

1202
00:53:51,666 --> 00:53:52,847
And so there were a lot of people

1203
00:53:52,887 --> 00:53:53,967
who would come on board later

1204
00:53:53,987 --> 00:53:56,208
who simply were not available to be involved yet.

1205
00:53:56,929 --> 00:54:01,374
So it was a small, tight-knit group of design, art, and engineering,

1206
00:54:02,055 --> 00:54:05,138
and everybody had a pretty much equal say

1207
00:54:05,359 --> 00:54:07,641
in all of the decisions that we were making at that point.

1208
00:54:07,661 --> 00:54:09,764
And that really continued throughout the production.

1209
00:54:09,784 --> 00:54:12,447
I think if you were to ask people on the Gambit team,

1210
00:54:13,388 --> 00:54:18,111
they would all tell you that they felt personally invested in the game because of that.

1211
00:54:18,171 --> 00:54:21,814
They didn't feel like they were executing someone else's vision.

1212
00:54:22,154 --> 00:54:24,956
It was our vision together. It was our game.

1213
00:54:25,056 --> 00:54:27,438
And I think that is a huge part of the success.

1214
00:54:27,478 --> 00:54:29,920
I think you can feel it in the way that the game turned out.

