1272
00:57:24,213 --> 00:57:25,734
We knew it was going to be related to Gambit.

1273
00:57:25,954 --> 00:57:28,095
But the actual mechanics of the quest itself

1274
00:57:28,536 --> 00:57:30,897
were not the focus of the Gambit team.

1275
00:57:31,217 --> 00:57:31,457
OK.

1276
00:57:31,957 --> 00:57:32,178
Thank you.

1277
00:57:35,841 --> 00:57:39,384
I found myself kind of smiling to myself when you were explaining the player messaging for

1278
00:57:39,404 --> 00:57:43,506
the invasions, how many layers there were particularly, and that kind of started making

1279
00:57:43,526 --> 00:57:47,129
you think about your playtesting cadence and wondering if that was response to playtesting

1280
00:57:48,029 --> 00:57:51,592
because of the invasions announced, the Klaxon, the Red Fog, the HUD, etc.

1281
00:57:51,632 --> 00:57:52,913
It just sounded very familiar to me.

1282
00:57:53,013 --> 00:57:57,016
So I was wondering about your playtesting cadence and also kind of the percentage of

1283
00:57:57,056 --> 00:57:59,017
internal versus external playtesting that you did.

1284
00:57:59,537 --> 00:57:59,818
on the mob.

1285
00:58:00,178 --> 00:58:00,398
Great.

1286
00:58:00,438 --> 00:58:02,820
So the question is about how often do we playtest,

1287
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:05,362
and what's the ratio of internal and external playtests?

1288
00:58:06,083 --> 00:58:09,926
We, as a team, playtested with each other daily.

1289
00:58:11,147 --> 00:58:13,649
We played the game for an hour every day together.

1290
00:58:14,330 --> 00:58:16,732
And unless the builds somehow weren't working out,

1291
00:58:16,792 --> 00:58:17,532
sometimes that happens.

1292
00:58:18,533 --> 00:58:19,934
So we were playing it all the time.

1293
00:58:20,835 --> 00:58:22,596
And that gave us a really good pulse

1294
00:58:22,957 --> 00:58:24,818
on where things were or weren't.

1295
00:58:25,899 --> 00:58:30,341
But we also had more late in the process,

1296
00:58:30,601 --> 00:58:34,122
we had some external testers and some user research going on,

1297
00:58:34,802 --> 00:58:37,663
bringing some people in to see how new players were exposed

1298
00:58:37,683 --> 00:58:39,724
to it, both players who were new to Destiny

1299
00:58:39,784 --> 00:58:41,525
and players who were experienced in Destiny.

1300
00:58:41,585 --> 00:58:43,946
How did they differ in their reactions to the mode?

1301
00:58:43,986 --> 00:58:44,766
What did they understand?

1302
00:58:44,826 --> 00:58:45,766
What did they not understand?

1303
00:58:45,786 --> 00:58:48,487
And there were user surveys after one game,

1304
00:58:48,607 --> 00:58:50,748
after two games, after three and five.

1305
00:58:51,288 --> 00:58:54,029
What do you know about the mode now that you didn't know before?

1306
00:58:54,109 --> 00:58:54,929
And so that helped us.

1307
00:58:55,610 --> 00:58:59,835
understand where our messaging was failing and where we needed to shore things up.

1308
00:59:00,335 --> 00:59:04,860
And we knew that invasion was just a critical mechanic to the game mode, and we had to make

1309
00:59:04,900 --> 00:59:10,246
it very, very clear when that was happening because it felt, for a while, like before

1310
00:59:10,286 --> 00:59:12,889
all that feedback goes in, of course, you're just playing it on trust.

1311
00:59:13,410 --> 00:59:15,371
You know that, oh yeah, later we're going to do stuff.

1312
00:59:15,391 --> 00:59:16,392
We're going to make this better.

1313
00:59:16,772 --> 00:59:18,314
But meanwhile, all we have is a little thing

1314
00:59:18,334 --> 00:59:20,215
at the bottom of the screen that says invader,

1315
00:59:20,595 --> 00:59:21,676
or whatever it might have been.

1316
00:59:21,776 --> 00:59:23,137
So it was really easy to miss.

1317
00:59:23,538 --> 00:59:25,759
And so we knew just from playing those early iterations

1318
00:59:25,799 --> 00:59:27,000
that we need more here.

1319
00:59:27,060 --> 00:59:29,883
