01:00:31,268 --> 01:00:32,649
I would love to be able to flip a switch

1343
01:00:32,689 --> 01:00:33,830
and just get a thousand voices.

1344
01:00:33,910 --> 01:00:34,731
It doesn't work that way.

1345
01:00:35,091 --> 01:00:36,152
Sure, at the office I can get it,

1346
01:00:36,232 --> 01:00:38,174
but not on real live code.

1347
01:00:40,215 --> 01:00:45,916
We're constantly playing the game ourselves and feeling it and evaluating what we want

1348
01:00:45,956 --> 01:00:47,376
to change and what feels right.

1349
01:00:47,936 --> 01:00:51,297
I think we like, there are a lot of things about Gambit Prime that we think work really

1350
01:00:51,317 --> 01:00:51,457
well.

1351
01:00:51,497 --> 01:00:56,078
We really like the fact that in one round it feels like lengthening the round and then

1352
01:00:56,138 --> 01:00:59,159
making it one round has just about the right length to it.

1353
01:01:00,899 --> 01:01:02,600
But there are things we might want to tweak.

1354
01:01:02,640 --> 01:01:05,640
We're looking at things like, hey, is the primeval phase...

1355
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:08,141
versus the motes phase?

1356
01:01:08,181 --> 01:01:09,522
Are they adequately balanced?

1357
01:01:09,963 --> 01:01:15,308
It seems a lot of the time like the invader and the defending

1358
01:01:15,348 --> 01:01:16,289
team are in sync.

1359
01:01:16,669 --> 01:01:18,230
So you'll get to that well of light

1360
01:01:18,491 --> 01:01:20,973
at the same time that the invader comes over and over

1361
01:01:21,033 --> 01:01:23,215
again by just you're in the right rhythm.

1362
01:01:23,515 --> 01:01:25,097
And so we're looking at maybe changing that up

1363
01:01:25,197 --> 01:01:26,798
so that there's a little more variety there.

1364
01:01:28,119 --> 01:01:30,481
Is the amount that the primeval is healed?

1365
01:01:32,136 --> 01:01:35,098
the is having to be the same amount in prime,

1366
01:01:35,358 --> 01:01:37,560
the right decision as it is in gambit.

1367
01:01:38,180 --> 01:01:40,002
There are a lot of things that we can tune

1368
01:01:40,322 --> 01:01:41,403
and we're looking at all of those things,

1369
01:01:41,483 --> 01:01:43,885
but so far, I mean, it's still so early

1370
01:01:44,405 --> 01:01:47,107
that we're kind of taking a cautious approach,

